 "Ah, little Kazinski, I forgive you for everything.
 You're the best thing to have happened to this team."

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Although Zorian was dying to study the orb in more detail, he had reluctantly
 decided to leave the orb in Daimen's hands for now.
 Trying to take it away would probably spark another fight and it wasn't like
 he had enough time to truly devote himself to its study right now.
 The attack on the Ibasan base beneath Cyoria was fast approaching, which meant
 that both Zach and Zorian would be forced to devote the majority of their
 energies into that for the next couple of days.

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"I have to say this whole thing makes me feel very conflicted," Zach said as
 they left the group.

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Why?" Zorian asked curiously.

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Well, on one hand, we only found the orb so quickly because Daimen pointed us
 at the right spot to start at," Zach said.
 "So if we ever get out of the time loop, the right thing to do would probably
 be tell him how to get it as a thanks for his help."

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"But?" Zorian prompted.

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"I really like the idea of having my own portable palace," Zach said with a
 dreamy grin.

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Zorian snorted derisively.
 "You shouldn't get excited just yet.
 For all we know the ruins really are full of slumbering giant hydras or
 something."

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"That just makes me more excited," Zach said.
 "That thing was a great opponent.
 Clearing a whole nest of them would be amazing."

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Oh, right.
 For a moment he had forgotten who he was talking with.

\end_layout

