 Ibasans would realize what was coming and raise the alarm.
 However, Alanic's suggestion made a lot of sense and he knew more about these
 sort of mass engagements than they did.
 If he thought a few more hours spent interrogating Sudomir wouldn't doom the
 operation, he was probably right.

